  "prompt": "Who is best hockey player of 2015?",
  "response": "In 2015, **Carey Price**, the goaltender for the Montreal Canadiens, was widely recognized as one of the top hockey players. He was awarded the **Hart Memorial Trophy** as the NHL's Most Valuable Player (MVP) for the 2014-2015 season. Price's exceptional performance between the pipes was instrumental in leading his team to success and earning him this prestigious accolade.\n\nAdditionally, **Jamie Benn** of the Dallas Stars won the **Art Ross Trophy** as the league's leading scorer that season, amassing 87 points (28 goals and 59 assists). His offensive prowess made him one of the standout players of the year.\n\nOther notable players from 2015 include **Sidney Crosby** of the Pittsburgh Penguins and **Alexander Ovechkin** of the Washington Capitals, both of whom continued to demonstrate elite skill and leadership on the ice.\n\nIt's important to note that the title of \"best\" player can be subjective and may vary based on specific criteria such as scoring, leadership, defensive abilities, and overall impact on the game.",
